Virgin Media Inc. (VMED) , the U.K.â€™s
second-largest pay-television company, said first-quarter
operating profit climbed 7.6 percent as it shifted customers
towards higher-speed broadband products.  Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, amortization
and other charges in the three months ended March rose to 376
million pounds ($614 million). Analysts had predicted operating
